328
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:20,881
Well, I want my money back.

329
00:25:21,419 --> 00:25:23,387
I want my money back, now.

330
00:25:23,455 --> 00:25:25,582
That money went to the capital
campaign for the new wing.

331
00:25:25,657 --> 00:25:27,454
- It's already been spent.
- Then unspend it.

332
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:28,618
I'm sorry.

333
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:32,626
We could maybe discuss an extension
of the money that you owe, but...

334
00:25:34,432 --> 00:25:36,229
I want my money back.

335
00:25:36,434 --> 00:25:38,994
That's not possible.

336
00:25:44,409 --> 00:25:45,967
Come on, baby, let's get out of here.

337
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:48,512
You're too good for this lousy school.

338
00:25:52,984 --> 00:25:53,973
Mom?

339
00:25:56,588 --> 00:25:58,453
Leave me alone.

340
00:26:04,963 --> 00:26:06,555
For God's sake, Ma.

341
00:26:07,365 --> 00:26:08,662
Are you OK?

342
00:26:08,733 --> 00:26:09,825
They dropped the charges.

343
00:26:09,901 --> 00:26:11,732
I have to fill out a form. No big deal.

344
00:26:11,803 --> 00:26:12,963
No big deal? I'm running for Congress.

345
00:26:13,038 --> 00:26:14,699
Do you have any idea
what this is gonna do to me

346
00:26:14,773 --> 00:26:16,400
