347
00:26:16,474 --> 00:26:19,875
What could you possibly need so bad
that you had to steal it?

348
00:26:19,945 --> 00:26:21,173
Never mind, I don't wanna know.

349
00:26:21,246 --> 00:26:22,941
- Socks.
- Socks?

350
00:26:25,483 --> 00:26:27,280
Dad left you a fortune. What are
you thinking?

351
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:29,343
You know, it's been one ridiculous
stunt after another with you

352
00:26:29,421 --> 00:26:32,356
for the last six months. Dad's gone,
just get over it.

353
00:26:32,424 --> 00:26:33,686
You know what? Leave her alone.

354
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:35,055
She's OK, that's all that matters.

355
00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:37,754
Thank God Mom's fine. She's a
criminal, but thank God she's OK.

356
00:26:37,829 --> 00:26:40,798
Next thing you know she's gonna be
telling us she's a crack whore.

357
00:26:40,865 --> 00:26:43,026
I gotta keep this out of the press.

358
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:45,300
You know what? Just get out of here.

359
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:46,962
Go worry about your image,
I'll handle this.

360
00:26:47,038 --> 00:26:49,768
Yeah. Good. I gotta make sure
this stays buried.

361
00:26:50,375 --> 00:26:52,468
- Thanks a lot, Mom.
- Mmm-hmm.

362
00:26:58,116 --> 00:26:59,743
What were you thinking?

363
00:27:00,418 --> 00:27:02,852
I just wanted to feel alive again.

364
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:09,857
Nathan only cares about himself.

365
00:27:09,928 --> 00:27:13,557
Your father was the same way.
Alpha dogs, both of them.

366
00:27:13,999 --> 00:27:17,400
You, in the meantime,
for all your selflessness,

367
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:20,199
and sitting with dying people...

368
00:27:21,072 --> 00:27:23,632
What? You're gonna retire on what you make?

369
00:27:23,708 --> 00:27:25,335
Maybe I'll shoplift my socks.

370
00:27:25,410 --> 00:27:26,672
Don't get smart.

371
00:27:26,745 --> 00:27:29,646
When you put everyone else
first, you end up last.

372
00:27:29,714 --> 00:27:32,205
You always put Nathan first,
he took advantage.

373
00:27:32,283 --> 00:27:35,616
Yeah, it wasn't you that was just
pushing him right out in front of me?

374
00:27:35,687 --> 00:27:37,712
He takes up more space than you.

375
00:27:37,789 --> 00:27:39,120
Demanded more attention.

376
00:27:39,557 --> 00:27:41,548
And besides, it's not my fault,
you allowed it.

377
00:27:41,626 --> 00:27:43,457
He's my brother. I love him.

378
00:27:43,828 --> 00:27:45,728
Love is overrated.

379
00:27:45,864 --> 00:27:48,458
He loves me, too. I know him.

380
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:49,994
We've always been close.

381
00:27:50,068 --> 00:27:51,330
Rose-colored glasses.

382
00:27:51,403 --> 00:27:52,893
That's cruel, Mom.

383
00:27:54,572 --> 00:27:57,302
Look, since Dad died, I know you've
been feeling free to speak your mind,

384
00:27:57,375 --> 00:28:00,811
but it wouldn't hurt to edit
yourself, every once in a while.

385
00:28:00,879 --> 00:28:02,972
I'm sorry if the truth hurts.

386
00:28:03,882 --> 00:28:07,181
I'm just saying you hero-worshipped him.

387
00:28:07,252 --> 00:28:09,152
And those feelings were never returned.

388
00:28:09,220 --> 00:28:12,485
You're wrong. It's biological,
and I can't help it, we're...

389
00:28:13,525 --> 00:28:14,958
...we're connected.

390
00:28:19,064 --> 00:28:22,864
I never told you this, but when
Nathan had his accident,

391
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:24,763
I knew it.

392
00:28:24,836 --> 00:28:26,030
We all got the same call.

393
00:28:26,104 --> 00:28:27,628
No, I'm saying before the call,

394
00:28:27,706 --> 00:28:30,470
like he was telling me, 300 miles away.

395
00:28:30,542 --> 00:28:34,000
I woke up, and I knew that he'd been hurt.

396
00:28:41,019 --> 00:28:44,682
I hate it here. She doesn't even
have any books to read.

397
00:28:44,756 --> 00:28:45,882
Baby, I'll be right back,

398
00:28:45,957 --> 00:28:47,390
I'm just gonna go and
pack up a few things.

399
00:28:47,459 --> 00:28:49,586
We should really go see Dad.

400
00:28:49,961 --> 00:28:51,519
What good would that do?

401
00:28:51,596 --> 00:28:52,585
He could help.

402
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:54,495
He should know that
someone's trying to hurt us.

403
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:57,797
Your dad's not in any position
to help us right now.

404
00:28:58,069 --> 00:29:00,970
Look, I made some mistakes,
I admit it.

405
00:29:01,039 --> 00:29:02,631
Mom, what'd you do?

406
00:29:05,744 --> 00:29:10,443
Hey. I need you to know that I would
never let anything happen to you.

407
00:29:10,815 --> 00:29:12,077
I promise.

408
00:29:12,183 --> 00:29:15,619
Mom, why'd you look at yourself
like that in the fish tank?

409
00:29:18,790 --> 00:29:20,087

410
00:29:23,661 --> 00:29:26,323
- How long?
- Just a couple hours, tops.

411
00:29:26,397 --> 00:29:28,831
There's some ice cream in the fridge.

412
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:30,597
Go ahead.

413
00:29:33,905 --> 00:29:36,669
- What happened?
- I went to see Linderman.

414
00:29:36,741 --> 00:29:38,641
- How much?
- Thirty.

415
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:40,308
You gambling again?

416
00:29:40,378 --> 00:29:41,936
No, it's just bills.

417
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,373
And I used the rest to get Micah
into private school.

418
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:48,078
They didn't know what to do with him
at public, and I just...

419
00:29:48,153 --> 00:29:49,745
I needed them to think
that we had money.

420
00:29:50,755 --> 00:29:52,416
From the mob?

421
00:29:53,591 --> 00:29:54,819
Hell, Niki.

422
00:29:55,326 --> 00:29:56,691
You weren't born yesterday.

423
00:29:56,761 --> 00:29:58,353
I'm just two weeks overdue.

424
00:29:58,429 --> 00:30:00,693
I mean, I thought that I could
handle it, OK? It's just...

425
00:30:00,765 --> 00:30:04,223
- I'm under a lot of stress right now, OK?
- Gee, I wonder why?

426
00:30:05,870 --> 00:30:08,600
I feel like I'm kind of losing it a little bit.

427
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:11,271
I'm seeing things.

428
00:30:12,076 --> 00:30:13,065
Like?

429
00:30:13,711 --> 00:30:15,975
Like I keep feeling like
someone's watching me.

430
00:30:16,047 --> 00:30:18,277
Yeah, Linderman wants his money back,

431
00:30:18,349 --> 00:30:20,874
so he sends some mouth-breather
that's gonna put you in the hospital.

432
00:30:20,952 --> 00:30:22,920
No, it is someone else.

433
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:26,185
It's someone that I can't see.

434
00:30:27,725 --> 00:30:29,716
Does this make any sense to you?

435
00:30:34,332 --> 00:30:35,321
No.

436
00:30:37,969 --> 00:30:39,095
I'm sorry, you know what?

437
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:40,194
But I'll tell you what does...

438
00:30:40,271 --> 00:30:41,329
I shouldn't be telling you this.

439
00:30:41,406 --> 00:30:42,964
No, no, let me tell you
what does make sense.

440
00:30:43,041 --> 00:30:46,875
You need to come up with that 30
grand plus interest, now.

441
00:30:46,945 --> 00:30:48,537
Or you gotta run.

442
00:30:50,114 --> 00:30:51,240
Watch him.

443
00:30:53,384 --> 00:30:54,476
All right.

444
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,469
Hiro.

445
00:31:47,005 --> 00:31:49,030

446
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:07,557
Cool, huh?

447
