486
00:36:07,398 --> 00:36:08,490
I'm sorry!

487
00:36:09,267 --> 00:36:10,529
There was a big bust this morning.

488
00:36:10,601 --> 00:36:12,330
Can we still make it?

489
00:36:12,403 --> 00:36:16,464
Sure. Six minutes ought to be plenty
of time to face our marital problems.

490
00:36:17,408 --> 00:36:19,433
And you're the one that
wanted to do this, remember?

491
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:20,977
No, I wanted this for us, OK?

492
00:36:21,045 --> 00:36:22,376
You're unhappy, that's a problem.

493
00:36:22,446 --> 00:36:23,970
Oh, right, it's my fault.

494
00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:26,243
No, I didn't mean that.

495
00:36:29,987 --> 00:36:32,854
I didn't pass. Again.

496
00:36:35,359 --> 00:36:38,419
If you think that makes
a difference to me, then...

497
00:36:38,629 --> 00:36:40,654
I never put any pressure
on you to move up.

498
00:36:40,731 --> 00:36:41,720
I don't care.

499
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,697
I just want you to be happy for once.

500
00:36:43,768 --> 00:36:44,928
I want to be where the action is.

501
00:36:45,002 --> 00:36:48,028
I've told you this. I'm not
gonna retire a beat cop.

502
00:36:49,774 --> 00:36:51,605
People get their dreams, why can't I?

503
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:53,371
We've been together 11 years, Matt.

504
00:36:53,444 --> 00:36:54,570
I've made my dreams come true.

505
00:36:54,645 --> 00:36:56,943
How long are we supposed to wait for yours?

506
00:36:57,014 --> 00:36:58,447
Why don't you just tell them the truth?

507
00:36:58,516 --> 00:36:59,881
Yeah, that's a great idea.

508
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:01,213
I'll just walk in there and tell them

509
00:37:01,285 --> 00:37:02,582
I can barely read.

510
00:37:02,653 --> 00:37:04,052
I mean, half the words I see backwards,

511
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:05,247
