00:57:30,146 --> 00:57:32,376
A homeless dude, on our way to school.

766
00:57:32,449 --> 00:57:34,974
We thought he was dead, but he wasn't.

767
00:57:36,386 --> 00:57:38,115
I thought Dad was coming home today.

768
00:57:38,188 --> 00:57:40,383
Well, I was gonna surprise you.

769
00:57:40,457 --> 00:57:43,688
He finished up early, he's coming
home tonight. Isn't that great?

770
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:45,625
Just in time to read
my report card.

771
00:57:45,695 --> 00:57:48,789
So what about you, Claire,
do anything special today?

772
00:57:54,137 --> 00:57:56,765
I walked through fire and I didn't get burned.

773
00:58:01,744 --> 00:58:03,302
What the hell is that supposed to mean?

774
00:58:03,379 --> 00:58:04,539
God, you're so crazy sometimes.

775
00:58:04,614 --> 00:58:05,842
Lyle.

776
00:58:08,785 --> 00:58:11,618
I think I know exactly what you mean.

777
00:58:11,721 --> 00:58:14,849
Oh, here I am, talking dogs again.

778
00:58:14,924 --> 00:58:17,893
And you go and say
something really profound.

779
00:58:18,995 --> 00:58:21,964
We come up against all kinds
of fires in our lives,

780
00:58:22,031 --> 00:58:25,194
and when we test ourselves
and face our fears,

781
00:58:25,835 --> 00:58:27,803
we usually don't get burned.

782
00:58:28,571 --> 00:58:31,267
You are very wise, sweetheart.

783
00:58:31,341 --> 00:58:36,210
Whatever it is you did, I'm proud of you.
And so is Mr. Muggles.

784
00:58:36,279 --> 00:58:38,042
He's just so proud of Claire.

785
00:58:38,114 --> 00:58:39,741
Aren't we? We're proud of Claire.

786
00:58:39,849 --> 00:58:42,317
Yes, we're so proud of Claire, aren't we?

787
00:58:42,385 --> 00:58:43,909
She's the best.

788
00:58:48,458 --> 00:58:50,085

789
00:58:50,426 --> 00:58:54,192

790
00:59:15,919 --> 00:59:16,908
Hiro.

791
00:59:54,524 --> 00:59:55,513
Hiro!

792
00:59:55,658 --> 00:59:56,647
Oi!

793
01:00:10,373 --> 01:00:11,965
What are you looking for?

794
01:00:12,041 --> 01:00:13,303
Morphine.

795
01:00:13,376 --> 01:00:14,775
What for?

796
01:00:15,111 --> 01:00:16,476
I need you to come
with me someplace.

797
01:00:16,546 --> 01:00:17,604
Where?

798
01:00:17,680 --> 01:00:18,874
You'll see.

799
01:00:19,248 --> 01:00:21,478
Look, there's... There's something
I need to tell you.

800
01:00:21,551 --> 01:00:22,950
Now that is gonna have to wait.

801
01:00:23,019 --> 01:00:25,817
No. Look, I need to tell you
about this, OK?

802
01:00:25,888 --> 01:00:27,685
I need to stop living for other people.

803
01:00:27,757 --> 01:00:30,487
My whole life I've had no idea
what I'm supposed to do,

804
01:00:30,560 --> 01:00:33,222
what I'm supposed to be, if I
even have a destiny of my own.

805
01:00:33,296 --> 01:00:35,560
I promise you we will
talk about this later, OK?

806
01:00:35,632 --> 01:00:38,157
But right now I really
need you to come with me.

807
01:00:38,234 --> 01:00:42,193
You're a nurse, you can give
out a shot, you can help him.

808
01:00:42,271 --> 01:00:43,260
Help who?

809
01:00:44,741 --> 01:00:47,574
I thought we could go to the movies
this Saturday,

810
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:52,411
maybe try on some shoes
at the new mall in Gardendale.

811
01:00:54,717 --> 01:00:55,706
Sure.

812
01:00:58,154 --> 01:00:59,781
I love you, Mom.

813
01:01:01,190 --> 01:01:02,179
But?

814
01:01:05,895 --> 01:01:07,362
No buts. I just...

815
01:01:07,730 --> 01:01:09,721
I just wanted to tell you that.

816
01:01:10,433 --> 01:01:13,402
Now you think I'm trying to be
your best friend again, admit it.

817
01:01:13,469 --> 01:01:14,458
No.

818
01:01:15,104 --> 01:01:18,938
It's all right, we can go to the
movies together. It's no big deal.

819
01:01:19,008 --> 01:01:21,943
I just miss you, that's all.

820
01:01:24,280 --> 01:01:28,546
I wanna be your mom, I wanna
give you advice.

821
01:01:28,618 --> 01:01:31,086
But I don't wanna push you away.

822
01:01:31,154 --> 01:01:32,985
I want advice, I do.

823
01:01:34,390 --> 01:01:37,018
I won't push you away, I promise.

824
01:01:39,162 --> 01:01:40,527

825
01:01:41,864 --> 01:01:46,665
I just don't think you should be so
worried about fitting in all the time.

826
01:01:47,503 --> 01:01:49,664
About being so popular.

827
01:01:49,739 --> 01:01:52,469
I don't want to see you
make mistakes like I did.

828
01:01:52,542 --> 01:01:56,000
I wanted to be someone more
interesting than I am.

829
01:01:56,746 --> 01:02:00,273
You are interesting. You breed
show dogs. Whose mom does that?

830
01:02:01,150 --> 01:02:04,119
No, I wanted to hitchhike across Europe.

831
01:02:04,487 --> 01:02:09,186
Study art. Fall in love with
some... poetry-quoting Frenchman.

832
01:02:10,159 --> 01:02:12,889
Not that your dad isn't
wonderful, but my point is,

833
01:02:12,962 --> 01:02:16,295
you should know who you are
and know that it's enough.

834
01:02:16,365 --> 01:02:18,595
'cause who you are is special.

835
01:02:22,071 --> 01:02:23,197
About that.

836
01:02:25,274 --> 01:02:27,367
There's something I need to say.

837
01:02:28,344 --> 01:02:32,405
Something I never talked about 'cause
I thought it would upset you and Dad.

838
01:02:32,515 --> 01:02:36,246
Sweetheart, you can say
anything to us, you know that.

839
01:02:38,755 --> 01:02:42,316
I think I'm old enough for you
to tell me who my real parents are.

840
01:02:45,795 --> 01:02:47,194
Of course you are.

841
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:53,925
Honey, I'm home.

842
01:02:54,370 --> 01:02:55,564
Your father.

843
01:02:58,674 --> 01:03:00,665
Hey, honey.

844
01:03:02,578 --> 01:03:05,376
Bad, Mr. Muggles. No.

845
01:03:06,048 --> 01:03:07,037

846
01:03:08,084 --> 01:03:10,382
- I'm glad you're home.
- Oh, me, too.

847
01:03:10,453 --> 01:03:13,650
I have such a headache. I slammed my head
getting out of a taxicab.

848
01:03:13,723 --> 01:03:14,815
Hi, Daddy.

849
01:03:17,627 --> 01:03:19,322
Hey, baby.

850
01:03:28,204 --> 01:03:30,468
I'll ask you one more time.

851
01:03:31,641 --> 01:03:33,871
And only one more time.

852
01:03:36,879 --> 01:03:38,039
Are you in?

853
01:03:41,083 --> 01:03:43,608
You found me seconds before I died.

854
01:03:45,021 --> 01:03:46,215
How is that possible?

855
01:03:46,289 --> 01:03:47,313
Fate.

856
01:03:49,792 --> 01:03:50,781
Fate...

857
01:03:56,465 --> 01:03:58,160
Maybe I was not meant to die.

858
01:03:58,234 --> 01:03:59,701
And maybe she was.

859
01:04:03,339 --> 01:04:05,170
Allah is merciful.

860
01:04:06,209 --> 01:04:09,804
He always has a plan.
He has a plan for you, Amid.

861
01:04:13,249 --> 01:04:14,841
You'll help us.

862
01:04:18,221 --> 01:04:20,018
It's your purpose.

863
01:04:26,662 --> 01:04:28,391
Bring me a glass of water.

864
01:04:29,131 --> 01:04:30,120

865
01:04:32,602 --> 01:04:34,126
The device you stole...

866
01:04:35,304 --> 01:04:36,828
you'll need more plutonium.

867
01:04:36,906 --> 01:04:38,032
How do you know that?

868
01:04:38,107 --> 01:04:39,699
And not just plutonium.

869
01:04:39,775 --> 01:04:42,972
You'll need enough P-235,
enough beryllium mixture,

870
01:04:43,045 --> 01:04:46,310
and you will need a lot more
to take out your target.

871
01:04:46,382 --> 01:04:48,646
- A lot more.
- Where do we get it from?

872
01:04:48,951 --> 01:04:50,316
Untie my hands.

873
01:04:54,957 --> 01:04:58,222
Six months ago, I woke to something extraordinary.

874
01:04:59,462 --> 01:05:00,588
An ability.

875
01:05:02,665 --> 01:05:03,654
A curse.

876
01:05:05,501 --> 01:05:09,028
Where it came from? I don't know.

877
01:05:11,140 --> 01:05:12,266
But now,

878
01:05:13,576 --> 01:05:16,067
I think it might be my purpose.

879
01:05:17,847 --> 01:05:22,443
I can emit 45,000 curies of radiation
from the palm of my hand.

880
01:05:26,722 --> 01:05:30,089
Enough to give cancer to those I love.

881
01:05:33,162 --> 01:05:37,155
Enough to detonate a five megaton
thermonuclear device.

882
01:06:11,634 --> 01:06:13,329

883
01:06:16,505 --> 01:06:19,736
Turn around! Get against the wall!
Get against the wall!

884
01:06:19,809 --> 01:06:22,573
Get against the wall, now!
Now, damn it! Move it!

885
01:06:25,214 --> 01:06:28,047
Hey, get your hands where I can see them.

886
01:06:31,253 --> 01:06:32,311
Amid!

887
01:06:32,388 --> 01:06:33,514
Matt?

888
01:06:33,589 --> 01:06:35,887

889
01:07:47,430 --> 01:07:49,193

890
01:07:49,665 --> 01:07:52,634
Hello, New York!

891
01:08:02,812 --> 01:08:04,905
You sure your ride's coming?

892
01:08:05,014 --> 01:08:06,447
Yeah, I'm sure.

893
01:08:06,515 --> 01:08:07,880
You be careful, son.

894
01:08:17,927 --> 01:08:19,417

895
01:08:57,867 --> 01:08:58,856
Sylar!

896
01:09:00,669 --> 01:09:03,502
I'm just saying it's impossible, OK?
Nobody can predict the future.

897
01:09:03,572 --> 01:09:04,596
I saw it with my own eyes, Peter.

898
01:09:04,673 --> 01:09:06,971
Isaac? I brought someone here to help.

899
01:09:07,042 --> 01:09:08,373
He's a nurse.

900
01:09:10,312 --> 01:09:11,301
Isaac.

901
01:09:13,883 --> 01:09:14,872
Isaac?

902
01:09:19,221 --> 01:09:20,210
Isaac?

903
01:09:22,591 --> 01:09:24,786
Maybe he went out. I don't know.

904
01:09:25,594 --> 01:09:26,583
Isaac.

905
01:09:27,730 --> 01:09:29,459
Simone!

906
01:09:29,532 --> 01:09:31,397
Oh, God.

907
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:32,489
OK.

908
01:09:33,202 --> 01:09:34,794
Oh, my God. Isaac?

909
01:09:34,870 --> 01:09:37,395
He's alive. Call 911.

910
01:09:37,473 --> 01:09:40,237
- I need a tourniquet.
- What have you done?

911
01:09:49,552 --> 01:09:54,114
Yeah, I'm at 215 Reed Street, number 7.

912
01:09:54,190 --> 01:09:58,092
I need an ambulance here immediately.
Someone has cut off his hand.

913
01:09:59,128 --> 01:10:02,928
No, no, he's conscious. Just barely.

914
01:10:04,166 --> 01:10:06,498
I know. Listen, could you just come?

915
01:10:08,170 --> 01:10:11,697
Did you find something? I think
there's some towels in the sink.

916
01:10:23,052 --> 01:10:26,544
OK, baby, it's OK, they're sending
an ambulance right now, OK?

917
01:10:26,622 --> 01:10:28,749
You just hang in there, OK?

918
01:10:35,397 --> 01:10:37,092
We have to stop it.

919
01:10:41,370 --> 01:10:43,702
- Oh, baby...
- We have to stop it.

920
01:10:55,651 --> 01:11:00,588
<i>This quest, this need to solve
life's mysteries.</i>

921
01:11:02,458 --> 01:11:04,016
<i>In the end, what does it matter</i>

922
01:11:04,093 --> 01:11:06,061
<i>when the human heart
can only find meaning</i>

923
01:11:06,128 --> 01:11:08,596
<i>in the smallest of moments?</i>

924
01:11:10,132 --> 01:11:13,568
<i>They're here. Among us.</i>

925
01:11:14,903 --> 01:11:19,567
<i>In the shadows, in the light. Everywhere.</i>

926
01:11:22,044 --> 01:11:24,376
<i>Do they even know yet?</i>

927
01:11:37,960 --> 01:11:41,760
All right, I'm here. Now what do you want?

928
01:11:44,333 --> 01:11:45,322
Peter?

929
01:11:52,374 --> 01:11:55,537
I've been up here all night
thinking about this.

930
01:11:56,278 --> 01:11:58,371
Thinking about my destiny.

931
01:11:59,381 --> 01:12:00,905
What are you doing, Pete?

932
01:12:00,983 --> 01:12:03,679
It's my turn to be somebody now, Nathan!

933
01:12:04,253 --> 01:12:06,551
Come on, Peter, quit screwing around!

934
01:12:56,205 --> 01:12:57,229
Peter!

935
01:12:57,306 --> 01:12:58,466

936
01:12:59,174 --> 01:13:00,368
Peter, hang on.

937
01:13:02,044 --> 01:13:05,309
How did you... You're flying.
You're flying!

938
01:13:05,381 --> 01:13:06,712
I don't know.

939
01:13:07,216 --> 01:13:08,877
I don't know. Oh, God.

940
01:13:09,585 --> 01:13:10,984
- Peter.
- Nathan!